    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Isn't it more important to address how dangerous it is for pedestrians and cyclists to coexist with the current traffic climate?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Isn't it more important to address how dangerous it is for pedestrians and cyclists to coexist with the current traffic climate?</p>
        <p>The Transportation Department needs to be proactive in pedestrian safety by widening sidewalks and installing traffic calming devices.  The result would be fewer parking spots and a more livable city. Improving neighborhood quality of life by cutting traffic noise and congestion should be important to the health and welfare of all New Yorkers, not just the ones who own cars.</p>
        <p>KAREN SOUTHERLAND  Greenwich Village</p>
      </block>
